          "defaultParameters": {
            "code": "# Step 3: Range-compressed — full view + adaptive-x crop in ONE iframe. The crop\n# is complex-upsampled so the range sinc sidelobes are smooth; F is chosen to keep\n# the upsampled crop under the vertex cap WITHOUT max-pooling (pool_b=False).\nrg_axis = (t_r - t_r_center) * c / 2\n_W = PEAK_HALF * view_scale\n\n_rc = np.where((rg_axis >= -_W) & (rg_axis <= _W))[0]\n_ac = np.where((az_pos  >= -_W) & (az_pos  <= _W))[0]\n_sub = s_rc[_ac[0]:_ac[-1]+1, _rc[0]:_rc[-1]+1]\n_rgx = rg_axis[_rc[0]:_rc[-1]+1]; _azx = az_pos[_ac[0]:_ac[-1]+1]\nF = crop_upsample_factor(len(_azx), len(_rgx))\n_mag = upsample_complex(_sub, F)\n_rgu = upsample_axis(_rgx, F); _azu = upsample_axis(_azx, F)\n\nsurface3d_pair(\n    s_rc, rg_axis, az_pos, 'Step 3: Range-compressed (full view)',\n    _mag, _rgu, _azu, 'Step 3: Range-compressed (x%d crop)' % F,\n    status_b='upsample x%d' % F, pool_b=False)\n",
            "label": "Plot: Range-compressed",
            "spec": "Display-only: 3-D dB surface of |s_rc| after range compression. Targets are now sharp in range (thin ridges) but still spread in azimuth. Peak-preserving max-pool downsample; Expand for full size."
          },
          "enabled": false,
          "codeCollapsed": true
        }
      },
      {
