          ],
          "defaultParameters": {
            "code": "# Step 4: Range-Doppler — full view + range-only adaptive-x crop in ONE iframe.\n# Vertical axis is Doppler [Hz] (not metres): only the range axis is cropped AND\n# upsampled. F (range-only) maximizes range detail under the vertex cap. The\n# range axis (the upsampled detail) is NEVER pooled; only the full-res Doppler\n# rows are max-pooled if needed (pool_b='rows') so the crop fits the cap without\n# coarsening the range sidelobes. Toggle Full/Crop.\nrg_axis = (t_r - t_r_center) * c / 2\n_W = PEAK_HALF * view_scale\n\n_rc = np.where((rg_axis >= -_W) & (rg_axis <= _W))[0]\n_sub = S_rd[:, _rc[0]:_rc[-1]+1]\n_rgx = rg_axis[_rc[0]:_rc[-1]+1]\nF = crop_upsample_factor(S_rd.shape[0], len(_rgx), range_only=True)\n_mag = upsample_complex_range(_sub, F)\n_rgu = upsample_axis(_rgx, F)\n\nsurface3d_pair(\n    S_rd, rg_axis, f_eta, 'Step 4: Range-Doppler (full view)',\n    _mag, _rgu, f_eta, 'Step 4: Range-Doppler (range x%d crop)' % F,\n    ylabel_a='Doppler [Hz]', ylabel_b='Doppler [Hz]',\n    status_b='upsample x%d (range)' % F, pool_b='rows')\n",
            "label": "Plot: Range-Doppler",
            "spec": "Display-only: 3-D dB surface of |S_rd| in the Range-Doppler domain. A target's energy lies on the RCM parabola (curved ridge across range vs Doppler) — this is why RCMC is needed. Axes: range [m] x Doppler [Hz]. Max-pool downsample."
          },
          "enabled": false,
          "codeCollapsed": true
        }
      },
      {
