          "defaultParameters": {
            "code": "# Step 5: After RCMC — full view + range-only adaptive-x crop in ONE iframe.\n# Vertical axis is Doppler [Hz]: only the range axis is cropped AND upsampled.\n# F (range-only) maximizes range detail under the vertex cap. The range axis (the\n# upsampled detail) is NEVER pooled; only the full-res Doppler rows are max-pooled\n# if needed (pool_b='rows') so the crop fits the cap without coarsening the range\n# sidelobes. Toggle Full/Crop in the plot.\nrg_axis = (t_r - t_r_center) * c / 2\n_W = PEAK_HALF * view_scale\n\n_rc = np.where((rg_axis >= -_W) & (rg_axis <= _W))[0]\n_sub = S_rd_rcmc[:, _rc[0]:_rc[-1]+1]\n_rgx = rg_axis[_rc[0]:_rc[-1]+1]\nF = crop_upsample_factor(S_rd_rcmc.shape[0], len(_rgx), range_only=True)\n_mag = upsample_complex_range(_sub, F)\n_rgu = upsample_axis(_rgx, F)\n\nsurface3d_pair(\n    S_rd_rcmc, rg_axis, f_eta, 'Step 5: After RCMC (full view)',\n    _mag, _rgu, f_eta, 'Step 5: After RCMC (range x%d crop)' % F,\n    ylabel_a='Doppler [Hz]', ylabel_b='Doppler [Hz]',\n    status_b='upsample x%d (range)' % F, pool_b='rows')\n",
            "label": "Plot: RCMC",
            "spec": "Display-only: 3-D dB surface of |S_rd_rcmc| after Range Cell Migration Correction. The curved RCM ridge from the previous step is now straightened (energy aligned to one range cell across Doppler). Axes: range [m] x Doppler [Hz]. Max-pool downsample."
          },
