          "defaultParameters": {
            "code": "# === Reflection / Raw Echo (NUFFT) ===\n# Self-contained NUFFT forward model. Builds the raw SAR echo s_raw (Na,Nr)\n# complex64 from POINT targets or an IMAGE target (2D reflectivity), using\n# finufft type-1 (GPU CuPy precompute + parallel CPU finufft). Replaces the\n# time-domain echo (old n7) as the sole echo generator. See SPEC for the math.\nimport numpy as np\nimport finufft\nimport cupy as cp\nimport concurrent.futures\nimport time as _time\n\nNUFFT_EPS = 1e-6      # accuracy floor (~120 dB). Lower to 1e-9 for higher.\nN_WORKERS = 8         # outer parallelism; finufft inner nthreads=1\n_t0 = _time.monotonic()\n\n# ---- 0. Self-contained clutter helper (was defined in the removed n7) ----\n# make_rand comes from n1 (always runs first). Box-Muller circular complex\n# Gaussian, sigma/sqrt(2) per I/Q, matching the old n7 / sar-visualizer.\ndef make_clutter_scatterers(count, rcs_db, half_az_m, half_range_m, seed, R0):\n    rnd = make_rand(seed)\n    sigma = (10.0 ** (rcs_db / 20.0)) / np.sqrt(2.0)\n    out = []\n    for i in range(int(count)):\n        az_m = (rnd() * 2 - 1) * half_az_m\n        sr_m = R0 + (rnd() * 2 - 1) * half_range_m\n        u1 = max(rnd(), 1e-12); u2 = rnd()\n        mag = sigma * np.sqrt(-2.0 * np.log(u1))\n        out.append(('clutter%d' % i, az_m, sr_m, mag * np.cos(2*np.pi*u2), mag * np.sin(2*np.pi*u2)))\n    return out\n\n# ---- 1. Build the source list: point targets, clutter, OR an image ----\n# target_mode comes from the Target Mode dropdown ('point' | 'image').\n# Fallback to 'point' if the GUI block hasn't run (keeps point-mode working).\n_mode = str(globals().get('target_mode', 'point')).strip().lower()\nTARGET_SEED  = 42\nCLUTTER_SEED = 2\nhalf = PEAK_HALF * view_scale          # display/scene half-extent [m]\n\nif _mode == 'image':\n    # IMAGE TARGET: each non-zero pixel becomes a scatterer. The image is\n    # centred on (az=0, slant=R0) and scaled to fit inside +/-0.9*half in both\n    # axes (so it stays within the View window). Pixel brightness -> reflectivity\n    # amplitude (real). invert_image=True => dark pixels are strong reflectors\n    # (good for line art); False => bright pixels are strong (photos).\n    from PIL import Image\n    _path = str(globals().get('image_path', '')).strip()\n    if not _path:\n        raise ValueError(\"target_mode='image' but image_path is empty — pick a file in the Image File block\")\n    _invert = str(globals().get('invert_image', 'true')).strip().lower() in ('1', 'true', 'on', 'yes')\n    _img = Image.open(_path).convert('L')\n    _gray = np.asarray(_img, dtype=np.float32)\n    if _invert:\n        _gray = 255.0 - _gray\n    _rows, _cols = np.where(_gray > 0)\n    if len(_rows) == 0:\n        raise ValueError(\"image has no non-zero pixels after invert=%s\" % _invert)\n    _H, _W = _gray.shape\n    # 1 pixel = 1 SAR resolution cell, so adjacent pixels fall in adjacent\n    # resolution cells and the image reads as a continuous shape (not a dotted\n    # grid). Slant-range res = c/(2B); azimuth res = La/2. The image then spans\n    # _W*_sp_rg x _H*_sp_az metres centred on (az=0, slant=R0); a large image\n    # can exceed the View window, which is correct (zoom the View to see it all).\n    _sp_rg = c / (2 * B)                     # slant-range resolution [m/pixel]\n    _sp_az = La / 2.0                        # azimuth resolution [m/pixel]\n    az_arr = (_rows - _H / 2.0) * _sp_az                 # azimuth offset [m]\n    sr_arr = R0 + (_cols - _W / 2.0) * _sp_rg            # slant range [m]\n    amp_arr = (_gray[_rows, _cols] / 255.0).astype(np.float64)\n    src_az = az_arr.astype(np.float64)\n    src_sr = sr_arr.astype(np.float64)\n    src_re = amp_arr                                     # real reflectivity\n    src_im = np.zeros_like(amp_arr)\n    NT = len(src_az)\n    print('IMAGE target: %s  %dx%d  %d scatterers (invert=%s)  spacing %.2f x %.2f m  window +/-%.0f m'\n          % (_path.split('/')[-1].split('\\\\')[-1], _H, _W, NT, _invert, _sp_rg, _sp_az, half))\nelse:\n    # POINT (+ optional clutter), identical placement to the old n7.\n    sources = [(n, a, s, 1.0, 0.0) for (n, a, s) in\n               make_point_targets(n_targets, half, half, TARGET_SEED, R0)]\n    n_clutter = int(clutter_n)\n    if n_clutter > 0:\n        sources += make_clutter_scatterers(n_clutter, clutter_rcs_db, half, half, CLUTTER_SEED, R0)\n    src_az = np.array([s[1] for s in sources], dtype=np.float64)\n    src_sr = np.array([s[2] for s in sources], dtype=np.float64)\n    src_re = np.array([s[3] for s in sources], dtype=np.float64)\n    src_im = np.array([s[4] for s in sources], dtype=np.float64)\n    NT = len(sources)\n    print('POINT sources: %d point + %d clutter  window=+/-%.0f m' % (n_targets, n_clutter, half))\n\n# ---- 2. Forward chirp spectrum: fft(ref_chirp), NOT conjugated, NO ifftshift ----\nchirp_fft = np.fft.fft(ref_chirp).astype(np.complex64)\n\n# ---- 3. GPU precompute weights + NUFFT coords; CPU parallel finufft ----\naz_t = cp.asarray(src_az, dtype=cp.float64)\nsr_t = cp.asarray(src_sr, dtype=cp.float64)\nrefl = cp.asarray((src_re + 1j * src_im).astype(np.complex64), dtype=cp.complex64)\naz_g = cp.asarray(az_pos, dtype=cp.float64)\nt_r_center = float(2 * R0 / c)\ninv_lam = 1.0 / float(lam)\n\nS_all = np.zeros((Na, Nr), dtype=np.complex64)\n# Pulse batch size bounds the (batch x NT) GPU arrays (image targets can have\n# hundreds of thousands of scatterers, so keep each batch's NT*batch modest).\ngpu_pb = max(4, min(512, int(2e9 / max(1, NT) / 32)))\n\ndef _nufft_chunk(x_chunk, w_chunk, row_start):\n    plan = finufft.Plan(1, (Nr,), eps=NUFFT_EPS, isign=1,\n                        dtype='complex64', nthreads=1)\n    out = np.empty((len(x_chunk), Nr), dtype=np.complex64)\n    for i in range(len(x_chunk)):\n        plan.setpts(x_chunk[i])\n        out[i] = np.fft.ifftshift(plan.execute(w_chunk[i]))\n    return row_start, out\n\nfor pstart in range(0, Na, gpu_pb):\n    pend = min(pstart + gpu_pb, Na)\n    azb = az_g[pstart:pend]\n    daz = azb[:, None] - az_t[None, :]\n    R_eta = cp.sqrt(sr_t[None, :]**2 + daz**2)\n    squint = cp.arctan2(daz, sr_t[None, :])\n    pat = cp.sinc(squint / theta_az) ** 2\n    tau = 2.0 * R_eta / c\n    x_b = cp.asnumpy((-2.0 * np.pi * Fs * (tau - t_r_center) / Nr)\n                     .astype(cp.float32))  # finufft complex64 plan wants float32 coords\n    carrier = cp.exp(-4j * np.pi * R_eta * inv_lam).astype(cp.complex64)\n    w_b = cp.asnumpy((refl[None, :] * pat.astype(cp.complex64) * carrier)\n                     .astype(cp.complex64))\n    del daz, R_eta, squint, pat, tau, carrier\n    cp.get_default_memory_pool().free_all_blocks()\n\n    nb = pend - pstart\n    sub = max(1, nb // N_WORKERS)\n    chunks = [(x_b[i:i+sub], w_b[i:i+sub], i) for i in range(0, nb, sub)]\n    with concurrent.futures.ThreadPoolExecutor(max_workers=N_WORKERS) as ex:\n        for fut in concurrent.futures.as_completed(\n                [ex.submit(_nufft_chunk, xc, wc, st) for xc, wc, st in chunks]):\n            st, res = fut.result()\n            S_all[pstart + st: pstart + st + len(res)] = res\n    print('\\r  pulses %d/%d (%.0f%%)' % (pend, Na, 100*pend/Na), end='')\n\n# ---- 4. chirp multiply + IFFT (GPU batch) -> s_raw ----\nS_gpu = cp.asarray(S_all)\nchirp_gpu = cp.asarray(chirp_fft)\ns_raw = cp.asnumpy(cp.fft.ifft(S_gpu * chirp_gpu[None, :], axis=1)).astype(np.complex64)\ndel S_gpu, chirp_gpu, S_all\ncp.get_default_memory_pool().free_all_blocks()\n\nprint('\\nNUFFT raw echo: mode=%s shape=%s NT=%d peak|s|=%.3f  (%.2fs)'\n      % (_mode, s_raw.shape, NT, float(np.abs(s_raw).max()), _time.monotonic() - _t0))",
            "label": "Reflection / Raw Echo (NUFFT)",
            "spec": "NUFFT-based forward model, mathematically equivalent to the time-domain echo (n7). Produces s_raw_nufft (Na,Nr) complex64 for direct comparison with s_raw.\n\nEquivalence: s_A[eta,n] = sum_j W_j * g(t_r[n]-tau_j), g = up-chirp ref_chirp shape, W_j = refl_j * antenna_pattern(squint_j) * exp(-4j*pi*R_eta_j/lam). NUFFT: m_j=(tau_j-t_r_center)*Fs; x_j=-2*pi*m_j/Nr; S[eta]=ifftshift(nufft1d1(x_j,W_j,Nr,isign=+1)); s_B[eta]=ifft(chirp_fft*S[eta]); chirp_fft=fft(ifftshift(ref_chirp)) (NOT conjugated).\n\nPorted from workspace_TargetSim TargetSim_FPGA n9 (GPU precompute + parallel finufft) + n32 (chirp*S -> IFFT). GPU hybrid: CuPy for distance/antenna/carrier (carrier in float64; r/lam ~ huge), CPU finufft (nthreads=1) parallelised with ThreadPoolExecutor. Caveat: circular conv (length Nr) vs n7 hard rect truncation -> only differs if a target pulse straddles a range edge (avoided by n2 grid margin at view_scale~1)."
          }
        }
      },
